HEADWORD: arugula
<hw>arugula</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>an erect European annual
(<spn>Eruca vesicaria</spn> <varn>sativa</varn>) of the mustard family,
often grown as a salad crop to be harvested when young and
tender.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> rocket, roquette, garden rocket, rocket salad, Eruca
sativa.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

